CatDescriptText: Cutline of images published in the Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 13, 1954, pg. 12 reads: " Hill City Contestants For Queen - Among the organizations sponsoring some of these lovely young teenagers, who are striving to wear the Hill City Queen's crown at the may Coronation Ball, are Alpha Alpha Omega Chapter of AKA, Omicron Psi Chapter of Omega Fraternity, Hill City Women's Auxiliary, and Schenley Heights Neighborhood Club.  In this group are, left to right...Letitia Averyth...Romaine Parham, sponsored by the Omega...-Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Letitia Averyth wearing eyeglasses and dark long sleeved sweater with brooch, posed in front of light colored background in Harris Studio for Hill City Teen Queen contest; Portrait of Romaine Parham wearing dark short sleeve sweater and three strand beaded necklace, posed in front of light colored background in Harris Studio for Hill City Teen Queen contest
